<P>Ok, I have now put some numbers together so we can actually compare =
these=20
monitors to each other. Admittedly, the numbers aren't exact since I =
don't know=20
how to gather this information myself. I just took the different ways =
they were=20
listed and did some simple math to generate the following table. <BR>
<P>The X axis is obviously the Monitor, the Y axis is the amount of =
deflection,=20
and the value is the time in microseconds to deflect that far. The last =
row is=20
the number of .05 inches per microsecond. I did not take into account =
that the=20
V2000 is only a 13" monitor since I figured the angle of deflection is =
all that=20
is really being measured. <BR>
<P>................................................................ =
<BR>: ::=20
6400 X : 6400 Y : 6100 X : 6100 Y : V2000 : G05 :=20
<BR>:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: =
<BR>: .5"=20
:: 6us : 6us : 10us : 13us : 4us : 5us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 1.0"=20
:: 8us : 8us : 20us : 27us : 8us : 10us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 2.0"=20
:: 16us : 21us : 40us : 53us : 16us : 20us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 4.0"=20
:: 30us : 42us : 80us : 106us : 32us : 40us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 8.0"=20
:: 62us : 94us : 160us : 213us : 64us : 80us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 10.5"=20
:: 84us : 131us : 210us : 279us : 84us : 105us :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>: 14.5"=20
:: 110us : 179us : 290us : 385us : 120us : 150us :=20
<BR>:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: =
<BR>: .05in=20
:: : : : : : : <BR>: /us :: 0.1325 : 0.08 : 0.05 : 0.0375 : 0.12 : =
0.0975 :=20
<BR>:.......::........:........:........:........:........:........: =
<BR>
<P>We still do not have any real numbers for the Amplifone XY monitor or =
the=20
Electrohome G08. Are these easily obtainable? Can you just put a scope =
on the=20
yoke and see how much time is between each peak? I guess we would need a =
special=20
test pattern for this? Any ideas? Or is this whole exercise a waste of =
time (I=20
know putting those damn .'s and :'s in were :). <BR>
<P>Jon <BR>
